space in the image history of the persian empire amol iran from the series iran revisited 1999 2009 an anonymous book its identity is suggested by the photograph's title lies open upon a counter in a fishmonger's office mazinani has focused the camera on this book the rest of the room its safes television sales receipts packing supplies are blurred the fishmonger himself is absent yet in the book's clear and active presence he lingers art architecture and design art & architecture library exhibitions back stanford university stanford california 94305 650 725 1064 terms of use copyright complaints
